- Right side: `(g ∘ f)(x) + (g ∘ f)(y) = g(f(x)) + g(f(y))`

We know `f` is a ring homomorphism, so `f(x + y) = f(x) + f(y)`.
Then `g(f(x + y)) = g(f(x) + f(y))`.
